      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalists would counter that their method is inherently *less* political because it grounds interpretation in objective historical fact, not in contemporary political desires. They argue that any judge who ignores the framers' original meaning is simply substituting their own political will for the law. Furthermore, the concept of \"original meaning\" is a neutral historical inquiry, not an ideological preference, which is what the critics are falsely accusing them of.",
