      "content": "fair enough. so if originalism is supposed to be a neutral way to keep judges in check, why does it feel like it's being used so much to roll back rights that people have relied on for decades? like, isn't there a risk that \"original meaning\" is just a convenient excuse to ignore modern social realities?",
